It is understood the man was apprehended following an altercation with police officers at an accident scene. CAPE TOWN A former Springbok rugby player has spent the weekend in a Seapoint jail after he was arrested last week.It is understood the man, who cannot be named until his first court appearance, was apprehended following an altercation with police officers at an accident scene.The suspect was part of the 1995 Rugby World-Cup team.The Police's Noloyiso Rwexana says, I can confirm that a 44-year-old man is expected to appear before the Cape Town Magistrates Court tomorrow, on charges of assault, intimidation and resisting arrest. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)